(44, 4, 37, 40, 19, 29, 29, NULL, 'Connection of Sacrifice and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forsaking land for a greater reward. Acts 4:37 illustrates the act of selling land, while Matthew 19:29 promises a hundredfold return for those who forsake lands for Jesus'' sake.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 37, 44, 4, 34, 35, 'laid it at the apostles’ feet', 'Connection of Generosity in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize the act of selling land and bringing the proceeds to the apostles. This highlights the communal spirit and support among believers, ensuring that no one lacked for their needs.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
